race.description: John Duff & Co The Lester Handicap
race.comment: SHOCKLETZ (5) was a bit disappointing second up when well supported as the $2.30 favourite second up at Flemington, striking a slowly run race where she got buried away and didn't have a whole lot of room to build momentum. That said, she was a bit plain off the sharp first up win. Suspect she wants all of this trip now and Ethan Brown going on is a positive. She can atone. HURRY CURRY (8) was very good fresh with 61kg at Moonee Valley when coming from last to grab a minor placing. Fitter now, she drops 7kg in weight and draws to sit much closer up in trip. BON MISTRESS (7) will find this easier than recent runs. Forgive the run on very heavy ground at Flemington, she can improve. HOWLIN' RAIN (1) was an easy Moe Cup winner last start and has claims, DARKNCONFIDENTIAL (3) next best.
